  "answer": "To refresh the list of available skills and ensure newly added ones are recognized, you need to place them in the correct directory and then reload the skill list.\n\nAccording to the Gemini CLI documentation, user-specific skills are discovered from the `~/.gemini/skills/` directory, not `~/.agents/skills/`.\n\nHere are the steps to make your new skills appear:\n\n1.  **Move your skills to the correct directory:** Ensure that your new skill directories are located within `~/.gemini/skills/`. For example, if you have a skill named `my-new-skill`, its path should be `~/.gemini/skills/my-new-skill/`.\n\n2.  **Reload the skills:**\n    *   **In an interactive session:** Use the slash command `/skills reload`.\n    *   **By restarting the CLI:** Closing and reopening the Gemini CLI will also trigger a rediscovery of skills.\n\nAfter performing these steps, your newly added skills should be discoverable and available for use with `activate_skill`.",
